So I ended up writing a blog post on how I go about naming things, as I think it's relevant to how we name these functions:

https://amboar.github.io/notes/2023/06/09/naming-functions-in-c.html

In that light, we're dealing with sockets, and we're in libpldm. So I think we should try to name these functions using the strategies outlined in the blog post:

```
int pldm_socket_sndbuf_init(struct pldm_socket_sndbuf *ctx);
int pldm_socket_sndbuf_set(struct pldm_socket_sndbuf *ctx, ...);
int pldm_socket_sndbuf_get(struct pldm_socket_sndbuf *ctx, ...);
```

In this case we can have `pldm_socket_sndbuf_init()` set up the maximum buffer size.
